rComments: Best professor i had in university.
Definately one of the best at UTSC. I didn't find him as hard as some made him out to be.

Absolutely one of the greatest profs ever in any subject!!! Has the ability to make history interesting, and tells it like a story. He is able to maintain your interest week in, week out for a solid two hours every week. What an amazing speaker. You'll find yourself taking 7 pages worth of notes back and front in every class! He's that good.
Never had a better prof. The best speaker I've ever heard from any discipline, from anywhere. Honestly, other profs can really take a leaf out of his book.
VERY HARD MARKER! WATCH OUT FOR HIM, EXCELLENT SPEAKER BUT HARD MARKER
One of the best professors UTSC has. Period.
Nice professor, however, VERY HARD MARKER!he expects a little to much from his students with essay writing, as not everyone can be as knowledgeable as him since hes specialized in the area :)

this guy is soo passionate about his subject. he lectures in a story tale manner that makes u want more out of class..if you have a chance to sneak in to a class do it...he;ll go down in history for best prof who can actually teach! ive never actually been excited to go to a class even midway during d semester. he marks difficult tho, still d best
Essay was worth way too much - 50% of your mark and there were no tutorials. The midterm was worth very little - 10% but he was very nice and did decide to boost the midterm marks up for everyone.
An amazing, inspiring man.

Indeed, Ecksteins is a great lecturer.  He makes everything sound so fascinating.  But he is a hard marker and offers students little help.  Not to mention that he favours certain students only.  He is also quite disorganized, especially in his senior level courses.

I love this man, but wow... he is one tough marker. He definitely knows what he's talking about and exudes a passion for his subjects that haven't been mastered by many other profs at utsc. He's funny, articulate, and is a terrific prof. Take his classes.
Excellent professor. world renowned. Best at UTSC. Passion flows deep within his veins for history. Excellent lecturer. Incorporates everything into his lecture especially art and culture.
SUCH A GOOD STORY TELLER. MAKES YOU WANT TO LEARN MORE
So interesting to listen to. You can really tell that he loves to teach. His love and understanding of history is inspiring.

He is one of the best prof. I've had and  also the reason I decided to specialize in the subject.  An hour lecture is not enough, I could spend the entire day listening to him lecture. His love for history really comes through in his lectures. NOt only is he extremely intelligent, but also very down to earth and approachable.

I have the greatest respect for Professor Eksteins.  He has a great teaching style that really captures your attention, and helps you to truly appreciate, not only the subject, but the discipline as well.  I would consider him a fine model of teaching in history.  UTSC is very fortunate to have him onboard.

Best History teacher I've had so far. Really funny and easy-going. He knows his stuff! One complaint about him is that sometimes he mixes up the dates...which can be kind of icky if you are studying the notes for exams....
He rules. His lectures are without a doubt the most interesting ever.
AMAZING!i have yet to see another professor who can make an hour fly by without me checking my watch.he brings us into his own world..
one of best ones ive had
A legend in his own mind.  And a huge head to match the ego.  He's a showman, but underneath he had no substance; won't go to bat for you.
No Comments
No prof has ever shown so much enthusiasm for his subject! Best history prof ever!
Makes the topics so interesting.  The hour flies by.
very passionate orator...makes an hour go by so fast.
Good lecturer.
Beats around the bush too much. Just get on with your point already!!
Wonderful!
very good lecturer...got a standing O from our class!
He has a passion for history that I have yet to see topped by any other instructor in any other subject. He's COOL!!!
excellent lecturer
Well spoken prof., interesting lectures, hard marker
